[We have already seen that Scottish heroin was being dumped. I gather
from contacts that there had been addict dissatisfaction with the
quality of the high being not "good". To keep their clients the
pushers would be pulling back that lot, and replacing it with a better
one in order to keep their clients. Then the inferior batch would be
remixed and/or shipped south, possibly at a bargain rate. This London
case indicates that the contaminated Scottish heroin is now in London.
Genomic confirmation of this London case is awaited. - Mod.MHJ]

